Interface IndexedCollection<P extends NamedProxy>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<P>, Iterable<P>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IndexedList<P>, IndexedSet<P>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    IndexedArrayList, IndexedArraySet, IndexedTreeSet

    public interface IndexedCollection<P extends NamedProxy>
extends Collection<P>

    A set that uses the names of Waters elements as an index.

    Author:
    Robi Malik

      • checkAllUnique

        void checkAllUnique(Collection<? extends P> collection)
        Checks whether this collection contains a collection of items. This method can be used when setting up a symbol table to ensure that no duplicate items have been created.
        Parameters:
        collection - The collection of items to be checked.
        Throws:
        NameNotFoundException - to indicate that the collection does not contain some item with the same name as some member of the input collection.
        ItemNotFoundException - to indicate that the collection contains an item with the same name as some member of the input collection, which is not the same object as that member.

      • checkUnique

        void checkUnique(NamedProxy proxy)
        Checks whether this collection contains an item. This method can be used when setting up a symbol table to ensure that no duplicate items have been created.
        Parameters:
        proxy - The item to be checked.
        Throws:
        NameNotFoundException - to indicate that the collection does not contain any item with the same name as the argument.
        ItemNotFoundException - to indicate that the collection contains an item with the same name as the argument, which is not the same object as the argument.

      • find

        P find(String name)
        Gets the item with the given name in this collection. In contrast to the get() method, this method does not return null if the collection does not contain any item with the given name, but throws an exception.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the item to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        The item with the given name.
        Throws:
        NameNotFoundException - to indicate that the collection does not contain any item with the given name.

        Gets the item with the given name in this collection.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        The item with the given name, or null if the collection does not contain any such item.

      • insert

        P insert(P proxy)
        Adds an item to this collection. This method makes sure that the collection contains an item equal to the given argument. If it does not yet contain such an item, it will attempt to add the argument.
        Parameters:
        proxy - The item to be added.
        Returns:
        The item equal to the argument that is in the collection. This may be the argument itself or another object equal to it that was there before.
        Throws:
        DuplicateNameException - to indicate that the item could not be added because the collection already contains a different item with the same name.

      • insertAll

        boolean insertAll(Collection<? extends P> collection)
        Adds a set of items to this collection. This method makes sure that the collection contains items equal to all the members of the given collection. It will attempt to add items not yet contained.
        Parameters:
        collection - A list of items to be added.
        Returns:
        true of the collection changed as a result of this call.
        Throws:
        DuplicateNameException - to indicate that some item could not be added because the collection already contains a different item with the same name.

      • insertAllUnique

        void insertAllUnique(Collection<? extends P> collection)
        Adds a set of items to this collection. In contrast to the insertAll() method, this method does not allow an item to be added if the collection already contains an item with the same name, no matter whether it is equal to the given argument or not. If some name is already taken, a DuplicateNameException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        collection - A list of items to be added.
        Throws:
        DuplicateNameException - to indicate that some item could not be added because the collection already contains an item with the same name.

      • insertUnique

        void insertUnique(P proxy)
        Adds an item to this collection. In contrast to the insert() method, this method does not allow an item to be added if the collection already contains an item with the same name, no matter whether it is equal to the given argument or not. If the name is already taken, a DuplicateNameException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        proxy - The item to be added.
        Throws:
        DuplicateNameException - to indicate that the item could not be added because the collection already contains an item with the same name.

      • reinsert

        void reinsert(NamedProxy proxy,
              String newname)

        Reinserts an item into this collection to see whether its name can be changed. This method removes the given item from this collection and inserts it under the given new name. The name of the item must be unchanged prior to this call.

        This method is intended to be called prior to changing the name of an item in a setName() method. An exception will be thrown if the item cannot be renamed in this collection. If this method returns successfully, the caller should change the item's name to restore consistency.

        Parameters:
        proxy - The item to be renamed.
        newname - The new name for the item.
        Throws:
        DuplicateNameException - to indicate that the item cannot be renamed because the collection already contains another item with the same name.
        ItemNotFoundException - to indicate that this collection does not contain the indicated item.

      • removeName

        P removeName(String name)
        Removes the item with the given name from this collection.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the item to be removed.
        Returns:
        The item that was removed, or null if the collection did not contain any item with the given name.
